ttps://kaiserfamilyfoundation.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/reportingmanualhivaidsukrainefull.pdf \u041a\u043b\u044e\u0447\u043e\u0432\u0456 \u0444\u0456\u0433\u0443\u0440\u0438 \u0443 \u0431\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0442\u044c\u0431\u0456 \u0437 \u0412\u0406\u041b/\u0421\u041d\u0406\u0414\u043e\u043c] // \u041f\u043e\u0441\u0456\u0431\u043d\u0438\u043a \u0437 \u0432\u0438\u0441\u0432\u0456\u0442\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0442\u0435\u043c\u0438 \u0412\u0406\u041b/\u0421\u041d\u0406\u0414\u0443. \u041a. : [[Kaiser Family Foundation|\u0424\u043e\u043d\u0434 \u0441\u0456\u043c'\u0457 \u041a\u0430\u0439\u0437\u0435\u0440]], 2005. \u0421. 67. {{in lang|uk}}</ref> and in the region of [[Eastern Europe]] and [[Central Asia]].<ref>[http://www.cphiv.dk/Portals/0/Reg-Tech-Consultation-the-Dissemination-of-Consolidated-Guidelines-on-the-Use-of-Antiretroviral-Drugs-for-HIV-Infection-in-eastern-European-and-central-Asian-Countries.pdf Regional technical consultation on the dissemination of consolidated guidelines on the use of antiretroviral drugs for treating and preventing HIV infection in Eastern European and Central Asian countries. Consultation report 29\u201331 October 2013]. [[Istanbul]] ([[Turkey]]), 2013. P. 45.</ref><ref>[http://www.unaids.org/en/resources/presscentre/featurestories/2015/june/20150602_yaravan Scaling up access to HIV testing and counselling in Eastern Europe and Central Asia]. Joint United Nations Programme on HIV/AIDS (UNAIDS). 3 June 2015.</ref> He is one of the founders of the national and international non-governmental organizations of PLWH, which collaborates with institutions of the [[United Nations]], the [[European Union]] and the [[United States|USA]], as well as with the [[Government of Ukraine|Cabinet of Ministers]] and the [[Presidential Administration of Ukraine]].<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/ukraine/Inficovani_diti_for_WEB.pdf \u0412\u0406\u041b-\u0456\u043d\u0444\u0456\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0456 \u0434\u0456\u0442\u0438: \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0447\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0434\u043e\u0433\u043b\u044f\u0434, \u043f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0456\u0447\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0456\u0434\u0442\u0440\u0438\u043c\u043a\u0430, \u0441\u043e\u0446\u0456\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0441\u0443\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0434, \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0439 \u0437\u0430\u0445\u0438\u0441\u0442] / &#91;\u0414\u0435\u0440\u0436. \u0441\u043e\u0446. \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0441\u0456\u043c'\u0457, \u0434\u0456\u0442\u0435\u0439 \u0442\u0430 \u043c\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0434\u0456; [[UNICEF|\u0414\u0438\u0442\u044f\u0447\u0438\u0439 \u0444\u043e\u043d\u0434 \u041e\u041e\u041d (\u042e\u041d\u0406\u0421\u0415\u0424)]]&#93;. \u041a., 2010. \u0421. 162. {{ISBN|978-966-2141-60-3}}. {{in lang|uk}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nVolodymyr Zhovtyak was born in [[Poltava]], Ukraine on 3 June 1973. He graduated from school No. 6 of Poltava (1990). He is a graduate of [[:uk:\u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0443\u043d\u0456\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442 \u043a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0438 \u0456 \u043c\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u0446\u0442\u0432|Kyiv National University of Culture and Arts]] (2005, management and economics faculty). He is the head of the Coordination Council of the charitable organization [[:uk:\u0412\u0441\u0435\u0443\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0436\u0430 \u043b\u044e\u0434\u0435\u0439, \u0449\u043e \u0436\u0438\u0432\u0443\u0442\u044c \u0437 \u0412\u0406\u041b/\u0421\u041d\u0406\u0414|All-Ukrainian Network of PLWH]] (since 2001);<ref>[http://network.org.ua/en/network/coordinating-council/ Coordinating Council]. All-Ukrainian Network of PLWH. 2014.</ref> the president of the international charitable organization Eastern Europe and Central Asia Union of PLWH (since 2005, the union has included organizations from 16 countries).<ref>[http://www.ecuo.org/en/ecuo/about/structure/ Structure]. Eastern Europe and Central Asia Union of PLWH. 2014.</ref> The place of his residence is the city of [[Kiev|Kyiv]].\n\nVolodymyr Zhovtyak is a member of advisory and consultative bodies under the [[President of Ukraine]] \u2014 the National Health Council (2006\u20132010);<ref>[http://www.kmu.gov.ua/control/publish/article?art_id=38122367 The President of Ukraine appointed the National Health Council, headed by Yuri Polyachenko]. Government Portal. 26 May 2006. {{in lang|ru}}</ref> the Coordinating Council on HIV/AIDS, Tuberculosis and Drug Addiction (2008\u20132010).<ref>[http://zakon4.rada.gov.ua/laws/show/220/2008 Presidential Decree No. 220/2008 of 17 March 2008 \"On the Coordinating Council on HIV/AIDS, Tuberculosis and Drug Addiction\"]. Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine. 2008. {{in lang|uk}}</ref> He is a member of advisory and consultative bodies of the Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine \u2014 the National Coordinating Council on HIV/AIDS (2005\u20132006, the chairman of the Committee on the Protection of the Rights of PLWH),<ref>[http://www.kmu.gov.ua/control/publish/article?art_id=16791379 Newly formed National Coordinating Council on HIV/AIDS started working]. Government Portal. 17 May 2005. {{in lang|uk}}</ref> the National Council to Fight Tuberculosis and HIV/AIDS (its deputy chairman since 2007).<ref>[http://health-ua.com/pics/pdf/ZU_2014_20/24-25.pdf \u0412\u0456\u0434\u0431\u0443\u043b\u043e\u0441\u044f \u0437\u0430\u0441\u0456\u0434\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f \u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438 \u0437 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0434\u0456\u0457 \u0442\u0443\u0431\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u043e\u0437\u0443 \u0442\u0430 \u0412\u0406\u041b-\u0456\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0456\u0457/\u0421\u041d\u0406\u0414\u0443] // \u0417\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432'\u044f \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438. 2014. \u2116 20. \u0421. 25. {{in lang|uk}}</ref>\n\nIn the late 90's, when he personally faced the problem of HIV, he became one of seven activists, having first founded an initiative group and then the All-Ukrainian Network of PLWH. As a HIV-problem insider, he realized that HIV-positive people in Ukraine had no access to treatment, care and support. That's why he began actively developing the civilian sector in Ukraine \u2014 he unified activists to defend his own legal rights, lobby for access to treatment, improve life quality of people living with HIV/AIDS in Ukraine.<ref>\u041b\u0438\u0442\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e, \u0412. \u041e\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0432\u044b \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0449\u0438 : \u0440\u0443\u043a\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0432\u0440\u0430\u0447\u0435\u0439. 3-\u0435 \u0438\u0437\u0434., \u0438\u0441\u043f\u0440. \u0438 \u0434\u043e\u043f. \u041a. : &#91;\u0418\u043d\u0436\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0433&#93;, 2006. \u0421. 18\u201361. {{ISBN|966-95147-7-0}}. {{in lang|ru}}</ref>\n\nIn 1999, a group of people with HIV/AIDS initiated changes in the country. Being supported by the [[United Nations Development Programme|UN Development Programme]] and the Counterpart Alliance for Partnership (a project by the [[United States Agency for International Development|U.S. Agency for International Development]]), the initiative group under the chairmanship of Volodymyr Zhovtyak started its work. Since the official registration of the charitable organization All-Ukrainian Network of PLWH (in 2001), he has been elected the head of the Coordination Council of the organization. Since its foundation, the Network has been the main organization, acting on behalf of PLWH community in Ukraine.<ref>[http://www.unaids.org/sites/default/files/media_asset/jc1305_ukraine_full_en_0.pdf A non-governmental organization's national response to HIV: the work of the All-Ukrainian Network of People Living with HIV] / Joint United Nations Programme on HIV/AIDS (UNAIDS). &#91;Kyiv, 2007&#93;. P. 6, 7, 9, 11, 20\u201321. {{ISBN|978-92-9173-597-6}}.</ref>\n\nVolodymyr Zhovtyak was repeatedly invited to speak at the [[Verkhovna Rada|Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine]] during public hearings on HIV/AIDS epidemic control.<ref>[http://lib.rada.gov.ua/LibRada/static/LIBRARY/povni_text/parlament_sluhan/alkohol.html Parliament proceedings \"Social and economic problems of HIV/AIDS, drug addiction and alcoholism in Ukraine and the ways to resolve them\" (verbatim record)]. The Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine: library bibliographical resources. 2003. {{in lang|uk}}</ref> He is a member of the editorial board Lyudi i Vich (People and HIV, {{lang-ru|\u041b\u044e\u0434\u0438 \u0438 \u0412\u0418\u0427}}), having 5 reeditions; the author of articles in thematic periodicals and numerous mass media interviews.<ref>[[#Literature]], [[#External links]].</ref>\n\n==Social activity==\nVolodymyr Zhovtyak is a member of special sessions of the [[United Nations General Assembly]] (2001, 2006, 2008, 2011, 2012). He was a delegate from Ukraine at the first Special Session of the UN General Assembly on HIV/AIDS ([[New York City|New York]], 2001). His joining the delegation as a representative of PLWH community of the country took place a month after the official registration of the All-Ukrainian Network of PLWH.<ref>A non-governmental organization's\u2026 P. 4, 20.</ref> The second Special Session of the UN General Assembly on HIV/AIDS (2011), in which he participated,<ref>[http://www.un.org.ua/en/information-centre/news/1330 Ukraine's participation in the UN General Assembly session on AIDS: the official delegation shares its vision and messages for the meeting]. United Nations in Ukraine. June 2011.</ref> adopted the Political Declaration on HIV and AIDS.<ref>[http://www.unaids.org/sites/default/files/sub_landing/files/20110610_UN_A-RES-65-277_en.pdf Political Declaration on HIV and AIDS: intensifying our efforts to eliminate HIV and AIDS]. Resolution adopted by the General Assembly on 10 June 2011. United Nations.</ref>\n\nThe collaboration of the All-Ukrainian Network of PLWH under the chairmanship of V. Zhovtyak with [[Elton John AIDS Foundation]] began from the moment of the Network's official registration in 2001. The foundation offered financial aid to the Network's services programs for HIV.<ref>Bakalec, L. [http://www.radiosvoboda.mobi/a/965376.html The singer Elton John called for more active measures against AIDS in Ukraine]. [[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]]. 18 June 2007. {{in lang|uk}}</ref>\n\nV. Zhovtyak is actively engaged in discussions on social policy, respect for human rights and discrimination against HIV-positive people in Ukraine. In 2002, the All-Ukrainian Network of PLWH launched a vast campaign to cut [[Management of HIV/AIDS|antiretroviral drugs (ARD)]] prices. In May 2002, Volodymyr Zhovtyak, with the support of [[Joint United Nations Programme on HIV/AIDS|UNAIDS]], participated in negotiations between the country's government, several institutions of the UN and transnational pharmaceutical companies. Due to the consolidated attitude of the Network's activists, the pharmaceutical companies had to reduce prices by 75% with time.<ref>A non-governmental organization's\u2026 P. 12\u201313.</ref>\n\nSince 2003, Volodymyr Zhovtyak has participated in Board meetings of [[the Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria]]. He was the first representative of the civil society in the delegation of Eastern Europe and Central Asia at the Fund board. He suggested changing the regulation on participating in the work of delegations. Due to this initiative, each of 24 countries of the region could have 2 of its representatives in the delegation \u2014 one on behalf of the government, the other \u2014 on behalf of the civil society.<ref>[http://eecaconstituency.org/uimages/sheets/EECA%20Constituency%20-%20Terms%20of%20Reference.pdf Terms of reference]. The Eastern Europe and Central Asia Constituency, the Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria. 2003.</ref> Therefore, the civil society could participate in the work of the delegation. He was personally involved in getting to Ukraine over a half-billion dollars of gratuitous financial aid,<ref>[http://www.ukrgazeta.com/ua/3216/ The Global Fund is worried over the policy conducted by Ukraine]. Ukrainska Hazeta. 25 January 2011. {{in lang|uk}}</ref> offered since 2003 by the Global Fund to combat the epidemic of AIDS and tuberculosis (for buying drugs, preventive measures, care and support).<ref>[http://www.un.org.ua/en/information-centre/news/542-2007-08-23 Grant agreement with the Global Fund to finance the new Programme counteracting HIV/AIDS in Ukraine for 2007\u20132012 signed]. United Nations in Ukraine. 23 August 2007.</ref><ref>[http://www.kmu.gov.ua/control/publish/article?art_id=247971613 The Global Fund gave to Ukraine almost 134 million dollars to fight against AIDS and tuberculosis]. Government Portal. 24 February 2015. {{in lang|uk}}</ref>\n\nAs the president of the international charitable organization Eastern Europe and Central Asia Union of PLWH (since the moment of its foundation in 2005), Volodymyr Zhovtyak has contributed to advocacy of access to ARD therapy in Eastern Europe and Central Asia, consulted representatives of PLWH community of the region on establishing and managing organizations of PLWH, represented their interests in international institutions.<ref>[http://www.news.tj/tj/node/1439 V. Zhovtyak, \"Common sense should prevail\"]. Asia-Plus ([[Dushanbe]], [[Tajikistan]]). 12 August 2010. {{in lang|ru}}</ref> In the context of the [[Lithuania]]n [[Presidency of the Council of the European Union|presidency of the EU Council]], with the support of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Lithuania, the association Positive Life, in collaboration with Eastern Europe and Central Asia Union of PLWH held an international forum \"HIV in Europe and neighboring countries\" ([[Klaip\u0117da]], Lithuania, 2013).<ref>[http://ecuo.org/ru/orc/video/2013/08/01/sotrudnichestvo-bez-granic-vostok-vstretil-zapad-v-klajpede/ Collaboration without borders. East met West in Klaipeda]. Eastern Europe and Central Asia Union of PLWH. 1 August 2013. {{in lang|ru}}</ref> At the suggestion of V. Zhovtyak, the forum adopted an appeal to European governments, adjacent states and the Global Fund Board, signed by PLWH organizations of 17 countries of the region.<ref>[http://www.eurohiv2013.eu/ru/ Resolution of participants of forum \"EuroHIV 2013\"]. Forum \"HIV in Europe and neighboring countries\". 27 July 2013. {{in lang|ru}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 November 2005, a presentation of the joint UNAIDS/WHO report, AIDS Epidemic Update 2005, for the first time took place in Ukraine.<ref>[http://www.un.org.ua/en/information-centre/news/503-2005-11-18 New joint UNAIDS/WHO report, AIDS Epidemic Update 2005, was presented on November 21, 2005 in Kyiv]. United Nations in Ukraine. November 2005.</ref> The [[Secretary-General of the United Nations|UN Secretary-General's]] special envoy professor Lars Kallings, and the head of the UN Theme Group on HIV/AIDS in [[Russia]], representative of the [[United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime|UN Office on Drugs and Crime]] Flavio Mirella came to Kyiv. The UN envoy Lars Kallings was received by the President of Ukraine [[Viktor Yushchenko]], L. Kallings was accompanied by UNAIDS country coordinator Ani Shakarishvili, Ukraine's health minister Yuri Polyachenko and the head of the Coordination Council of the All-Ukrainian Network of PLWH Volodymyr Zhovtyak.<ref>[http://www.un.org.ua/files/un_bulletin_10-12.pdf UNSG's Special Representative on HIV/AIDS meets with President Yushenko and launches 2005 AIDS Epidemic Update in Ukraine] // UN bulletin. United Nations in Ukraine. 2005. October\u2013December. P. 4.</ref> In the follow-up discussion, the President reported on Ukraine's getting international support for AIDS prevention as well as on his personal control of the problem.<ref>Hordienko, S. M. [http://www.health-ua.org/archives/health/1186.html HIV/AIDS is an international problem]. Zdorovie Ukrainy. November 2005. {{in lang|ru}}</ref>\n\nIn 2006, Volodymyr Zhovtyak, as a representative of Ukraine, participated in negotiations with the [[Clinton Foundation|Clinton Foundation HIV/AIDS Initiative]]. The project comprised representatives of [[Deutsche Gesellschaft f\u00fcr Internationale Zusammenarbeit|German Agency for International Cooperation]] (a project of the [[Cabinet of Germany|Federal Government of Germany]]), Policy (a project of the European Union), the U.S. Agency for International Development. The Clinton Foundation through its acquisition fund provided to Ukraine access to low prices on diagnostic equipment and ARD-drugs for HIV-infected people.<ref>[http://likuemo.in.ua/zikavo_ztaty/page,2,33713-V-Ukraine-startoval-pervyiy-v-Ukraine-proekt-Fonda-Iniciativ-Klintona-po-VICh-SPIDu.html The first in Ukraine project of the Clinton Foundation HIV/AIDS Initiative was launched in Ukraine]. Drug reference. 11 November 2006. {{in lang|uk}}</ref> There was signed an agreement on Ukraine's access to wider practical use of ARD therapy. When signing the agreement, the Fund manager and former [[President of the United States|President of the USA]] [[Bill Clinton]] said that it would help to increase the number of people, who receive medical treatment.<ref>[https://www.clintonfoundation.org/main/news-and-media/press-releases-and-statements/press-release-clinton-foundation-hiv-aids-initiative-announces-partnership-with.html Press release: Clinton Foundation HIV/AIDS Initiative announces partnership with AntiAIDS and the Victor Pinchuk Foundation]. Clinton Foundation. September 2006.</ref>\n\nIn 2010, as a member of the public, V. Zhovtyak opened the [[XVIII International AIDS Conference, 2010|XVIII International AIDS Conference (AIDS 2010)]] in [[Vienna]] ([[Austria]]).<ref>[http://kff.org/global-health-policy/event/aids-2010-press-conference-opening-press-conference/ AIDS 2010: press conference: opening press conference]. Henry J. Kaiser Family Foundation. 18 July 2010.</ref> The conference delegates were greeted also by the [[President of Austria|Austrian President]] [[Heinz Fischer]], federal minister of health [[Alois St\u00f6ger]], the Deputy President of the [[South Africa|Republic of South Africa]] [[Kgalema Motlanthe]] and [[European Commissioner for Health and Food Safety|EU Commissioner of Health and Consumer Policy]] [[John Dalli]].<ref>[http://www.aids2010.org/WebContent/File/Day1_AIDS2010_Opening_Press_Release_18_July_2010_FINAL2__ENG.pdf Official press release]. XVIII International AIDS Conference. 18 July 2010.</ref> The international conference aimed at resolving global problems of HIV/AIDS, was held with the support of UNAIDS and the Global Fund.<ref>[http://www.aids2010.org/Default.aspx?pageId=193 Sponsors and supporters]. XVIII International AIDS Conference. July 2010.</ref>\n\nV. Zhovtyak participated in the 61st session of the [[World Health Organization]] Regional Committee for Europe (September 2011, [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijan]], a member of the national delegation of Ukraine). In the person of Volodymyr Zhovtyak, representatives of the civil society for the first time took part in a session of the WHO Regional Committee for Europe.<ref>[http://issuu.com/network_of_plwh/docs/vseukrayinska_mereja_ljv_na_mijnaro \u0412\u0441\u0435\u0443\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0441\u0435\u0442\u044c \u041b\u0416\u0412 \u043d\u0430 \u043c\u0435\u0436\u0434\u0443\u043d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u043e\u043c \u0443\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0435. \u0418\u044e\u043d\u044c 2011 \u2014 \u043e\u043a\u0442\u044f\u0431\u0440\u044c 2012]. [[Alushta|\u0410\u043b\u0443\u0448\u0442\u0430]], 2012. \u0421. &#91;9&#93;. {{in lang|ru}}</ref> The session adopted European Action Plan for HIV/AIDS 2012\u20132015 involving member states, civil society, donor and development agencies, non-governmental organizations and the [[European Commission]].<ref>[http://www.euro.who.int/__data/assets/pdf_file/0011/153875/e95953.pdf European Action Plan for HIV/AIDS 2012\u20132015] / World Health Organization, Regional Office for Europe. [[Copenhagen]] ([[Denmark]]) : World Health Organization, 2011. 70 p. {{ISBN|978-92-890-0252-3}}.</ref>\n\nSince July 2014 (when Ukraine was elected to the Board), Volodymyr Zhovtyak had been a member of the UNAIDS Programme Coordinating Board. The first Ukrainian delegation was headed by the Deputy Prime Minister of Ukraine [[Oleksandr Sych]].<ref>[http://www.moz.gov.ua/ua/portal/pre_20140701_c.html The delegation, headed by the Deputy Prime Minister of Ukraine Oleksandr Sych, participates in the session of the UNAIDS Programme Coordinating Board]. [[Ministry of Healthcare (Ukraine)|Ministry of Health of Ukraine]]. 1 July 2014. {{in lang|uk}}</ref> In December 2014, V. Zhovtyak participated in the 35th session of the Board that was opened in [[Geneva]] ([[Switzerland]]). The session dealt with creating an international policy to confront HIV/AIDS after 2015.<ref>[http://dssz.gov.ua/index.php/golovna/97-novyny/2420-delegatsiya-ukrajini-bere-uchast-u-roboti-koordinatsijnoji-radi-yunejds The delegation of Ukraine participates in the work of the UNAIDS Programme Coordinating Board]. [[:uk:\u0414\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 \u0437 \u043f\u0438\u0442\u0430\u043d\u044c \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0434\u0456\u0457 \u0412\u0406\u041b-\u0456\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0456\u0457/\u0421\u041d\u0406\u0414\u0443 \u0442\u0430 \u0456\u043d\u0448\u0438\u0445 \u0441\u043e\u0446\u0456\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e \u043d\u0435\u0431\u0435\u0437\u043f\u0435\u0447\u043d\u0438\u0445 \u0437\u0430\u0445\u0432\u043e\u0440\u044e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u044c|State Service of Ukraine on HIV/AIDS and Other Socially Dangerous Diseases]]. 9 December 2014. {{in lang|uk}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Literature==\n# \u0416\u043e\u0432\u0442\u044f\u043a, \u0412. [http://www.aidsalliance.org.ua/ru/library/our/aidsnws/pdf/aidsnews6.pdf \u0411\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u043e\u0439 \"\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0434\u043d\u0438\u043a\" \u0432\u043e\u043a\u0440\u0443\u0433 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043c \u0412\u0418\u0427/\u0421\u041f\u0418\u0414] // \u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0412\u0418\u0427/\u0421\u041f\u0418\u0414. 2002. \u0412\u044b\u043f. 3 (6). \u0421. 14. {{in lang|ru}}\n# [http://www.unesco.kz/publications/hivaids/IntoFocus8en.pdf NGO Zhapagat, working for the support of PLWHA in Temirtau, Karaganda Oblast, Kazakhstan] // Into Focus. [[Almaty]] ([[Kazakhstan]]), 2003. No. 8. P. 4.\n# [http://www.aidsalliance.org.ua/ru/library/our/peopleandhiv/pdf/ph3.pdf \u041b\u044e\u0434\u0438 \u0438 \u0412\u0418\u0427. \u041a\u043d\u0438\u0433\u0430 \u0434\u043b\u044f \u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0434\u0443\u0448\u043d\u044b\u0445] / \u0440\u0435\u0434. \u0441\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0442: \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0443\u0449\u0430\u043a \u041b., \u0411\u0430\u043b\u0430\u043a\u0438\u0440\u0435\u0432\u0430 \u041e., \u0416\u043e\u0432\u0442\u044f\u043a \u0412. \u0438 \u0434\u0440. \u0418\u0437\u0434. 3. \u041a. : &#91;\u041c\u0411\u0424 \"\u041c\u0435\u0436\u0434\u0443\u043d\u0430\u0440. \u0430\u043b\u044c\u044f\u043d\u0441 \u043f\u043e \u0412\u0418\u0427/\u0421\u041f\u0418\u0414 \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043d\u0435\"&#93;, 2004. 527 \u0441. {{ISBN|966-96099-5-X}}; \u0418\u0437\u0434. 4. 2006. 633 \u0441. {{ISBN|966-8978-29-3}}; 5-\u0435 \u0438\u0437\u0434. 2009. 704 \u0441. {{ISBN|978-966-8035-65-4}}. {{in lang|ru}}\n# Goei, Tanne de. [http://www.frauenundhiv.info/sites/default/files/material/72_blickpunkt_aids_2005.pdf_0.pdf AIDS ist nicht nur eine Epidemie : Volodymyr Zhovtyak] // Blickpunkt AIDS / Deutsche AIDS-Hilfe e.V. &#91;[[Berlin]]&#93; : Herausgeber Corinna Gekeler; Dirk Hetzel, 2005. P. 19. {{ISBN|3-930425-56-4}}. {{in lang|de}}\n# [http://www.un.org.ua/files/UNDP_Publication_web.pdf \u0412\u043e\u0437\u0432\u0440\u0430\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043a \u0436\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0438. \u0417\u0430\u043c\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0442\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043f\u0438\u044f \u0433\u043b\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u0441\u043f\u0435\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0438 \u0431\u044b\u0432\u0448\u0438\u0445 \u043f\u043e\u0442\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u044a\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043d\u0430\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0442\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432]. \u041a. : \u041f\u0440\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043c\u043c\u0430 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0438\u044f \u041e\u041e\u041d \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043d\u0435, 2007. \u0421. 12. {{in lang|ru}}\n# Zhovtyak, Vladimir. [http://www.undp.org/content/dam/undp/library/Democratic%20Governance/Beyond%20Transition-%20Towards%20Inclusive%20Societies.pdf Social exclusion of people living with HIV in Eastern Europe and the CIS] // Beyond transition towards inclusive societies. &#91;Regional human development report&#93; / published by United Nations Development Programme, Regional Bureau for Europe and CIS. [[Bratislava]] ([[Slovakia]]) : &#91;Valeur&#93;, 2011. P. 65. {{ISBN|978-92-95092-31-0}}.\n# Zhovtyak, Volodymyr. [http://www.gnpplus.net/assets/Annexs-8_Stigma-Index_Report_ENGL-copy.pdf Acknowledgements] // The people living with HIV Stigma Index : analytical report based on research findings. Kyiv : &#91;Engineering&#93;, 2011. P. 6. {{ISBN|978-966-2344-12-7}}.\n# [http://network.org.ua/upload/iblock/d9c/d9ca4617c64734c2e8c523e15e4b8879.PDF \u0417\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0447 \u0432\u0438\u0441\u043e\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0440\u0456\u0432\u043d\u044f \u0437 \u043f\u0438\u0442\u0430\u043d\u044c \u0412\u0406\u041b/\u0421\u041d\u0406\u0414\u0443: \u043a\u043b\u044e\u0447\u043e\u0432\u0456 \u0440\u0435\u0437\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438 \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0440\u0435\u0433\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0443] // \u0406\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0456\u0439\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0432\u0456\u0441\u043d\u0438\u043a \u0412\u0441\u0435\u0443\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0457 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0436\u0456 \u041b\u0416\u0412. 2011. \u2116 3 (60). \u0421. 1\u20133. {{in lang|uk}}\n# [http://library.khpg.org/files/docs/1372329735.pdf The State Penitentiary Service opened doors for civil society organizations of Ukraine] // [[Human rights in Ukraine|Human Rights In Healthcare \u2014 2012]]. Human rights NGOs report on respect for the right to health in Ukraine / The Legal Research and Strategy Institute. [[Kharkiv]] (Ukraine): Prava ludyny, 2013. P. 42.\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Volodymyr Zhovtyak}}\n* [http://www.armaids.am/photo/E-bulletin_AIDS_Conference_08.12.09_eng.pdf \"HIV/AIDS actual issues\" international conference]. National Center for AIDS Prevention of the Ministry of Health of [[Armenia]]. 8 December 2009.\n* [http://rian.com.ua/analytics/20091201/78246228.html HIV/AIDS in Ukraine: \"worse than in Africa\"]. [[RIA Novosti|RIA Novosti Ukraine]]. 1 December 2009. {{in lang|ru}}\n* [http://tsn.ua/ukrayina/ukrayinu-pozbavlyat-300-mln-dolariv-cherez-ignoruvannya-borotbi-zi-snidom.html Ukraine, ignoring the fight against AIDS, will be deprived of 300 million dollars]. [[:uk:\u0422\u0421\u041d|TSN]]. 25 January 2011. {{in lang|uk}}\n* [http://www.radiosvoboda.org/content/article/1892341.html HIV/AIDS is still a threat] (interview with V. Zhovtyak and N. Nizova). Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty. 1 December 2012. {{in lang|uk}}\n* [http://firstua.com/